The paper focuses on image restoration tasks using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new network architecture, which involves regulating the width of the network to balance feature extraction and generalization ability, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of skip-connections and the stabilization of the learning process, which could also fall under neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
